  "prompt": "What are some good TED talks on comedy?",
  "response": "Here are some TED Talks related to comedy:\n\n1. \"Inside the Mind of a Stand-up Comedian\" by Chris Rock\n\u2022 While technically not a TED Talk, this is a similar style presentation\n\n2. \"The Surprising Secret to Speaking with Confidence\" by Caroline Goyder\n\u2022 Discusses humor as a communication tool\n\n3. \"The Power of Vulnerability\" by Bren\u00e9 Brown\n\u2022 While not strictly about comedy, it discusses humor and human connection\n\n4. \"How to Sound Smart\" by Conor Neill\n\u2022 Includes insights about using humor effectively\n\n5. \"Why We Laugh\" by Sophie Scott\n\u2022 A neuroscientific look at the psychology of laughter\n\n6. \"Humor, Survival, and the Human Condition\" by Steve Kaplan\n\u2022 Explores comedy from a storytelling perspective\n\n7. \"The Surprising Science of Happiness\" by Dan Gilbert\n\u2022 Touches on humor's role in emotional well-being\n\nWhile not all of these are exclusively about comedy, they offer interesting perspectives on humor, communication, and human psychology. I recommend checking their descriptions to see which might interest you most.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these?",
